#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:1
msgid "Documentation framework"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:3
msgid ""
"We aim to build our documentation according to the [Diátaxis framework for "
"technical documentation](https://diataxis.fr), which divides documentation "
"into four categories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:5
msgid "[Tutorials](#tutorials)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:6
msgid "[Guides](#guides)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:7
msgid "[Reference](#reference)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:8
msgid "[Concepts](#concepts)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:10
msgid ""
"We've found that contributors struggle to understand the differences between "
"these categories, and while we _strongly_ recommend reading up on the "
"Diátaxis framework, we can summarize them as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:12
msgid "Reference"
msgstr "參考手冊"

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:14
msgid "Reference material should"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:16
msgid ""
"Focus on \"what's there\", simply listing which functions, classes, etc. "
"exist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:17
msgid ""
"Use terse language, with the text and layout optimized for scanning and "
"random access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:18
msgid "Show relevant and complete usage examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:19
msgid "Link to related items for better discoverability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:21
msgid "Tutorials"
msgstr "教學"

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:23
msgid ""
"Tutorials walk the user through a particular activity to teach them about "
"common tools and patterns in the ecosystem. While the activity itself is "
"important, the goal is also to connect the dots between other things the "
"reader has learned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:26
msgid ""
"The structure of tutorials should minimise the cognitive load on learners, "
"and actively avoid choices and opportunities for user errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:28
msgid "Guides"
msgstr "指南"

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:30
msgid ""
"Guides are a list of steps showing how to achieve a specific goal or solve a "
"specific problem. The goal is to help the reader reach a specific end, not "
"understand the underlying theory or broader context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:33
msgid ""
"A guide assumes that the reader already has the background to understand the "
"topic at hand and therefore doesn't need to explain the introduction of each "
"new concept."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:35
msgid "Concepts"
msgstr "概念"

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:37
msgid ""
"Concepts describe the internals of a piece of code or how to think about a "
"particular idea or entity in the ecosystem. A concept can also describe the "
"historical context behind why something works the way that it does today."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:40
msgid ""
"If you find yourself wanting to write about the nitty gritty details of how "
"something works, you most likely want to write an explanation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:42
msgid "Guides vs. Tutorials"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:44
msgid ""
"We find that contributors primarily struggle with the difference between a "
"Guide and a Tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:46
msgid "Here are several explanations to help you understand the difference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:48
msgid ""
"A guide is used in a \"working\" context where the reader just wants a "
"sequence of instructions to achieve an outcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:49
msgid ""
"In this context the reader may already know or may not care how or why these "
"instructions work, they just want to know what to do in order to achieve the "
"desired result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:50
msgid ""
"A tutorial is used in a \"learning\" context where the reader is following a "
"sequence of instructions to gain practice performing a certain task."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:51
msgid ""
"Some small bits of motivation or explanation are helpful in this context to "
"help a reader connect the dots with other things they may have already "
"learned, but the focus is on the activity, not on _how_ or _why_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:53
msgid "A helpful analogy is landing an airplane in two different contexts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:55
msgid ""
"Let's say the pilot is unconscious and you now have to land the plane to "
"avoid a crash landing. In this context you just want to know how not to die. "
"You don't care about how or why, you just want to be on the ground in one "
"piece. This is the context for a guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:60
msgid ""
"A pilot training in a flight simulator wants to practice landing the plane. "
"The pilot-in-training needs practice knowing when to deploy the landing "
"gear, when to adjust flaps, etc. Actually landing the plane during the "
"flight simulation is less important than learning the individual skills that "
"make up a successful landing. This is the context for a tutorial."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:65
msgid ""
"Finally, one last way of thinking about the difference between a how-to "
"guide and a tutorial is like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:66
msgid "Guide: \"step 1: do this, step 2: do that, etc\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../contributing/documentation/diataxis.md:67
msgid "Tutorial: \"take my hand as I show you how to do this\""
msgstr ""
